14/09/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski has appointed Lazar Kitanovski as the new head of the national intelligence agency, according to a statement issued Monday (13 September).
Kitanovski served as defence minister from 1997 to 1998, when Crvenkovski was prime minister.
The previous intelligence chief, Dragi Grozdanovski, resigned citing personal reasons.
(Vest - 14/09/04;
A1 TV - 13/09/04)
